	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Oct 31st 4:19 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84649><span id=Scholar>Troodon</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>700 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.36]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well keep in mind that the other idols require more expensive imbued gems than this, plains pebbles can be foraged for free.&nbsp;&nbsp;Granted, when you add in the cost of all the other ingredients, the difference isn't that significant, but that's probably the logic here.  Notice the stats tend to improve the more expensive the imbued gem is.  Compare this, to say, a golden idol of Mithaniel Marr, which uses an imbued diamond.<br><br>Edit:  However, think of it this way, these stats would be nice for druids and rangers, really.  Or clerics and pallys.  And those 4 classes make up the majority of Karana worshippers right there, hehe.  Think about who would likely be worshipping Karana, and this stats don't look so bad after all.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Apr 20 03:44:06 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Troodon, AKA Zararazu Twoflower, Level 59 Iksar Monk, Jaggedpine Defender, Solusek Ro<br><br>My profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426</a></td></td></tr>
